{"TopicId":177370,"ForumId":38,"TopicTitle":"Martian Packing List","CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-07T01:12:34Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-07T01:12:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn this game, we will try to think of things you might need on a pioneering trip to Mars that would not be immediately apparent. Please include some description of what the item or skill would be useful for. Here are some examples:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Martian colonists might find it useful to learn sign language, as a backup for their spacesuit radio.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. Since Mars receives a lot less sun energy than Earth, you probably wouldn\u0027t need to wear sun shades there very much.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. A simple household broomstick would likely suffice for cleaning dust off solar panels.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4. It would be a good idea to have some way of maintaining and harvesting a colony of cockroaches to cook and eat, as they are hardy and nutritious.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-07T05:41:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n5. Gauze. It\u0027s dusty there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221418074635_kak-sdelat-vatno-marlevuyu-po\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://kak-sdelat-vse.com/uploads/posts/2014-12/1418074635_kak-sdelat-vatno-marlevuyu-povyazku.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022314\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fraston","CreatedById":188565,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-07T15:58:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n6. guns. for propulsion. this would actually be quite useful, if you brought a\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n7. raft along. just be careful of people behind you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansonKerman","CreatedById":185809,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-07T17:37:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cfont face=\u0022Lucida Sans Unicode, Lucida Grande, sans-serif\u0022\u003E8. Some explosives, in case a\u00A0satellite found a \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u00A0cool \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/font\u003E\u003Cfont face=\u0022Lucida Sans Unicode, Lucida Grande, sans-serif\u0022\u003Emineral deposit far below the surface.\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-07T18:19:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n9. A flag - to plant\u003Cbr\u003E\n10.\u00A0A foot - to print.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-07T18:20:06Z\u0022 title=\u002208/07/2018 06:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 7, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T02:37:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n11. \u003Cspan\u003E:Several thermonuclear explosive devices. For melting a lot of ice, quickly.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E12. Now you\u0027ll\u00A0need sunglasses after all.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Chel","CreatedById":176173,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T02:53:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n13: Cat plushies. I have no idea why. Maybe for the kids? ???\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T03:11:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n14. A sled, to sled down Nilokeras Scopulus if it is smooth enough.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T03:52:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n15. Moar\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003Ethermonuclear explosive devices. For melting a lot of ice, quickly, and just for fun.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Orc","CreatedById":154404,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T07:20:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n16. Snacks. Moar Snacks. Moar moar Snacks. I think Jeb would agree.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n17. Orbital Solar focus mirrors for concentrating\u00A0 sunlight. Use that for melting the\u00A0South Pole, and if you can get the focus fine enough signing your name on the Martian terrain.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n18. von Neumann toolkit.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n19. Potatoes (read \u0022The Martian\u0022 by Andy Weir).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n20. A Kindle with a very BIG capacity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T13:32:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n21. Nearly forgot. A peeler.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002225754088-wooden-peeler-and-potatoes-on-w\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022300\u0022 src=\u0022https://us.123rf.com/450wm/jirkaejc/jirkaejc1402/jirkaejc140200086/25754088-wooden-peeler-and-potatoes-on-white-background.jpg?ver=6\u0022 width=\u0022450\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T13:35:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n22. Salt. That stuff in the ice is NOT OK to put on your potatoes...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n23. A piano. On a ship with several hundred tons of payload mass, you can probably spare 300 kg for an upright.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ARS","CreatedById":168061,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T13:46:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n24. Nuclear reactors and lots and lots of RTGs because solar panels simply isn\u0027t enough\u00A0there\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n25. Fans and vacuum cleaner, for dealing with\u00A0dust\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n26. Rocket launchers, for when you need to put a simple microsats quickly in orbit and need a portable launcher\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n27. Internet connection tower, can\u0027t live without it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T14:50:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n28. Pieces of copper and zinc. To make electricity if reactor is down\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022potato-battery-electrodes.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022343\u0022 src=\u0022https://d1ca4yhhe0xc0x.cloudfront.net/Files/8108/6/potato-battery-electrodes.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022300\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansonKerman","CreatedById":185809,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T14:54:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E29: A trash can. To barf in. Because Mars can make you feel that way. (this is just another Really Really Really Tall Building).\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kernel Kraken","CreatedById":181383,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T19:31:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n30: A fire extinguisher.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/hHXx8AmBwXg?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn case of an escape pod malfunction.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T20:05:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n31. A multi-tool. Because a real spaceman must have it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022victorinox_53509_swisschamp_xavt_multi_t\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.bhphotovideo.com/images/images1500x1500/victorinox_53509_swisschamp_xavt_multi_tool_pocket_1355518.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022768\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n32. One more multi-tool.\u003Cbr\u003E\nBecause otherwise how to screw a nut on a bolt with just one multi-tool?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022two-wrench-tighten-bolt-nut-22024963.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022533\u0022 src=\u0022https://thumbs.dreamstime.com/b/two-wrench-tighten-bolt-nut-22024963.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n33. Pliers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221200px-Tool-pliers.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022512\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Tool-pliers.jpg/1200px-Tool-pliers.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause otherwise what to do if forgot one multitool at home?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MDZhB","CreatedById":99243,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-10T13:22:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223429153\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177370\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533604354\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cubinator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/6/2018 at 9:12 PM, cubinator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince Mars receives a lot less sun energy than Earth, you probably wouldn\u0027t need to wear sun shades there very much.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, I\u0027m pretty sure that UV is a much bigger problem on Mars than on Earth, due to the thinner atmosphere and lack of ozone. So,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n34. Really good sunglasses.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-10T13:23:25Z\u0022 title=\u002208/10/2018 01:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 10, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by MDZhB\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansonKerman","CreatedById":185809,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-11T17:13:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E35: A list of chores. For chores.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-11T17:52:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n36. A manual override for the pod bay doors, in case of rogue AI.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n37. A list of paradoxes, in case of rogue AI.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansonKerman","CreatedById":185809,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-11T19:17:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E38: A reprogram on a disc,\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223432050\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177370\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534009970\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cubinator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, cubinator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nin case of rogue AI.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-11T21:28:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n39/ A discombobulator. To combobulate.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansonKerman","CreatedById":185809,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-12T14:44:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E40: Some plushies. For the kids.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E41: A Rubiks Cube. For anyone who\u0027s\u00A0like my dad.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kernel Kraken","CreatedById":181383,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-12T17:04:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n42: A copy of The Hitchiker\u0027s Guide to the Galaxy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-12T17:04:31Z\u0022 title=\u002208/12/2018 05:04  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 12, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Kernel Kraken\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IncongruousGoat","CreatedById":157062,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-12T17:10:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n43: A towel, to go with the copy of The Hitchiker\u0027s Guide to the Galaxy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n44: A slide rule, in case of calculator failure\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}